<TITLE> Who're PM's pick! </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 11 (bdnews24.com)  "Brazil or Argentina?" And the prime minister laughed. But the press corps persisted. The journalists had gathered at the prime minister's official residence for a press conference where Sheikh Hasina would give her reactions about the proposed budget for the next fiscal. When reporters asked if she would watch the inaugural ceremony, Hasina said, "But of course." "Why do you think I am getting done with all these formalities before the match starts?" Hours before the World Cup's inauguration, and once Hasina was done with her briefing, journalists popped the all important question  which was her favourite team. Hasina managed a laugh when another reporter suggestively asked if she supported Argentina and not Brazil. Perhaps not to spark another controversy, Hasina remained silent. She only moved her lips  as if to say 'Brazil'. But one could hardly be sure. A former cabinet secretary, and currently an adviser to the prime minister, HT Imam was at hand and came to the PM's rescue. True to the risk-averse nature that bureaucrats are famous for, he provided the diplomatic non-confrontational answer. "The prime minister will root for whichever team plays well." "Yes, yes, I will support whoever plays well," said Hasina in cue
